                    <item xml:id="a5">
                    <locus target="#4v" facs="005"/>
                    <desc>
                    “Our Holy mother Walatta Petros, died in her 40th year, in the year 7,165 on the 11th epact and the 19th Matqa [Jewish New Year, lit. Shofar, which is taken to be the analogue of the bell in Christian culture], in the fifth year of the reign of our Emperor Yohannes, lover of God in the year of Matthew, the evangelist. We wrote this book of Gadl because of a spirit of jealousy arose about our holy mother, Walatta Petros, to be read on the 17th of Ḫǝdar.” The owner is mentioned, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ገብራ ያዕቆብ</foreign>, Gabra Yaqob, also mentioned 35v, and 93r (where the wife is mentioned, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሜልኮል</foreign>)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <desc>
                    Digitized by Wendy Laura Belcher with Selamawit Mecca in January 2011 with a Canon Powershot outdoors at the Bäträ Maryam Monastery on Zage Pennisula on Lake Ṭana
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
